translate="no"/><figure id="00-04-03-78-repair-40-01-30-01-02-21-1-1-1" translate="no"><image dimension="F2 (85x85) #" href="../MergedPictures/ILL-000016731_c@[users[p077020[appdata[local[temp[aptexport[00-04-03-78-repair-40-01-30-01-02-21-1-1-1.png" style="width: 85.0mm; height: 85.0mm;" translate="no"/><illusnum>RDE-000323273-04-03-78-repair-40-01-30-01-02-21-1-1-1-000016731</illusnum></figure><para translate="yes">Remove the damaged part, by simultaneously heating with a heat stripper to destroy the bonding.</para></descsection></descbody></description><description id="d1e143" translate="no"><title translate="yes">Scouring</title><descbody translate="no"><descsection translate="no"><marklayer translate="no"/><figure id="00-04-03-132-repair-40-01-30-01-02-21-1-1-2" translate="no"><image dimension="F2 (85x85) #" href="../MergedPictures/ILL-000012996_c@[users[p077020[appdata[local[temp[aptexport[00-04-03-132-repair-40-01-30-01-02-21-1-1-2.png" style="width: 85.0mm; height: 85.0mm;" translate="no"/><illusnum>RDE-000323273-04-03-132-repair-40-01-30-01-02-21-1-1-2-000012996</illusnum></figure><para translate="yes">Scour the cement residue left on the vehicle.</para></descsection></descbody></description></description><description id="d1e157" translate="no"><title translate="yes">preparation before assembly</title><descbody translate="no"/><description id="d1e161" translate="no"><title translate="yes">Adjustment before assembly</title><descbody translate="no"><para translate="yes">Position the replacement part, adjust it and fix it using the locking pliers.<sieref href="x-wc://gie=OR:wt.part.WTPartMaster:3503961" translate="no"><linkdesc translate="no">body structure maintenance and adjustment tools : use</linkdesc><linkvalue translate="no">GIEMR-001610</linkvalue></sieref>             </para></descbody></description><description id="d1e169" translate="no"><title translate="yes">Marking and identifying the joints</title><descbody translate="no"><para translate="yes">Mark the joint areas.</para><para translate="yes">Remove the replacement part.</para></descbody></description><description id="d1e177" translate="no"><title translate="yes">Preparation of the joints on the replacement part</title><descbody translate="no"><para translate="yes">Sand using<technicalvalue translate="no"><value translate="yes">P320</value></technicalvalue>dry sand paper or a red abrasive pad, without removing the protection.</para><para translate="yes">Clean the internal joint face with surface cleaner.</para></descbody></description><description id="d1e190" translate="no"><title translate="yes">Preparation of the joints on the vehicle</title><descbody translate="no"><para translate="yes">Clean the internal joint face with surface cleaner.</para></descbody></description><description id="d1e196" translate="no"><title translate="yes">Apply the protection before assembly</title><descbody translate="no"><para translate="yes">Position the acoustic inserts in the hollow sections, if necessary.</para><para translate="yes">                <sieref href="x-wc://gie=OR:wt.part.WTPartMaster:3524920" translate="no"><linkdesc translate="no">soundproofing product before assembly : description</linkdesc><linkvalue translate="no">GIEMR-001673</linkvalue></sieref>             </para></descbody></description></description><description id="d1e205" translate="no"><title translate="yes">assembly</title><descbody translate="no"/><description id="d1e209" translate="no"><title translate="yes">Application of the bonding product</title><descbody translate="no"><descsection translate="no"><marklayer translate="no"/><figure id="00-03-04-8-repair-40-01-30-01-02-21-1-1-3" translate="no"><image dimension="F2 (85x85) #" href="../MergedPictures/ILL-000017795_c@[users[p077020[appdata[local[temp[aptexport[00-03-04-8-repair-40-01-30-01-02-21-1-1-3.png" style="width: 85.0mm; height: 85.0mm;" translate="no"/><illusnum>RDE-000323273-03-04-8-repair-40-01-30-01-02-21-1-1-3-000017795</illusnum></figure><para translate="yes">Apply the relevant bonding product for the type of joint concerned<sieref href="x-wc://gie=OR:wt.part.WTPartMaster:3476622" translate="no"><linkdesc translate="no">body structure bonding : precautions for the repair</linkdesc><linkvalue translate="no">GIEMR-000170</linkvalue></sieref>                   <sieref href="x-wc://gie=OR:wt.part.WTPartMaster:3528712" translate="no"><linkdesc translate="no">bodywork bonded assembly product : description</linkdesc><linkvalue translate="no">GIEMR-001822</linkvalue></sieref>                </para></descsection></descbody></description><description id="d1e224" translate="no"><title translate="yes">Fitting and adjusting the replaced parts</title><descbody translate="no"><descsection translate="no"><marklayer translate="no"/><figure id="00-04-03-131-repair-40-01-30-01-02-21-1-1-4" translate="no"><image dimension="F2 (85x85) #" href="../MergedPictures/ILL-000012995_c@[users[p077020[appdata[local[temp[aptexport[00-04-03-131-repair-40-01-30-01-02-21-1-1-4.png" style="width: 85.0mm; height: 85.0mm;" translate="no"/><illusnum>RDE-000323273-04-03-131-repair-40-01-30-01-02-21-1-1-4-000012995</illusnum></figure><para translate="yes">Position the part on the vehicle.</para><para translate="yes">Tighten the joint using C-clamps to flatten the seal and ensure bonding.</para><para translate="yes">Insert the plastic protector shims between the C-clamps and the part so that it is not marked.</para></descsection></descbody></description><description id="d1e239" translate="no"><title translate="yes">Finishing</title><descbody translate="no"><para translate="yes">Remove the excess cement with thinner before drying.</para><para translate="yes">Make the original associated joint ( see procedure corresponding to the relevant associated joint ).</para><noteR translate="no" type="note"><para translate="yes">Note:</para><para translate="yes">If the bonded joint is associated with a resistance welded joint, the joint face is not accessible using the spot welder and the spot welds are replaced by plug welds, the cement bead must be broken at the plug welds so as not to alter the spot quality.</para></noteR></descbody></description></description><description id="d1e255" translate="no"><title translate="yes">Special notes on roof Assembly: description</title><descbody translate="no"><descsection translate="no"><marklayer translate="no"/><figure id="00-03-04-35-repair-40-01-30-01-02-21-1-1-33" translate="no"><image dimension="F2 (85x85) #" href="../MergedPictures/ILL-000025846_c@[users[p077020[appdata[local[temp[aptexport[00-03-04-35-repair-40-01-30-01-02-21-1-1-33.png" style="width: 85.0mm; height: 85.0mm;" translate="no"/><illusnum>RDE-000323273-03-04-35-repair-40-01-30-01-02-21-1-1-33-000025846</illusnum></figure><para translate="yes">Apply a cement bead to the roof cross members.</para><para translate="yes">Apply a bead of<ingredientname translate="yes">high performance structural adhesive</ingredientname>over the whole internal joint face on the body side<sieref href="x-wc://gie=OR:wt.part.WTPartMaster:3485957" translate="no"><linkdesc translate="no">body structure bonding with hard mastic : description</linkdesc><linkvalue translate="no">GIEMR-000171</linkvalue></sieref>(MR400, 40F, Bonded connections).</para><para translate="yes">Smooth the<ingredientname translate="yes">high performance structural adhesive</ingredientname>using a small brush.</para></descsection><descsection appl="|||||||||||||||||||||||||||||||||||||||X44/TN||||||||||||||" translate="no"><marklayer id="marklayer-d1e277" translate="no"><mark id="MARK.REPAIR-40X01X30X01-02X21-1-1.1" translate="no"><mcomponent translate="no"><label translate="no"/></mcomponent><designation translate="no">1</designation></mark></marklayer><figure id="40-07-02-75-repair-40-01-30-01-02-21-1-1-34" translate="no"><image dimension="F1 (85x60) #" href="../MergedPictures/ILL-000029937_lay-000121091.png" style="width: 85.0mm; height: 60.0mm;" translate="no"/><illusnum>RDE-000323273-07-02-75-repair-40-01-30-01-02-21-1-1-34-000029937</illusnum></figure></descsection><descsection appl="|||||||||||||||||||||||||||||||||||||||X44/TOTOIL||||||||||||||" translate="no"><marklayer id="marklayer-d1e294" translate="no"><mark id="MARK.REPAIR-40X01X30X01-02X21-1-1.2" translate="no"><mcomponent translate="no"><label translate="no"/></mcomponent><designation translate="no">1</designation></mark></marklayer><figure id="40-07-02-186-repair-40-01-30-01-02-21-1-1-35" translate="no"><image dimension="F2 (85x85) #" href="../MergedPictures/ILL-000050184_lay-000121090.png" style="width: 85.0mm; height: 85.0mm;" translate="no"/><illusnum>RDE-000323273-07-02-186-repair-40-01-30-01-02-21-1-1-35-000050184</illusnum></figure><para translate="yes">Apply<ingredientname translate="yes">high performance structural adhesive</ingredientname>to the body side again at<markref format="dita" href="#d1e255/40-07-02-186-repair-40-01-30-01-02-21-1-1-35" scope="local" translate="no" type="figure">1</markref>.</para></descsection><?Pub Caret 0?><descsection translate="no"><marklayer translate="no"/><figure id="40-07-02-76-repair-40-01-30-01-02-21-1-1-42" translate="no"><image dimension="F1 (85x60) #" href="../MergedPictures/ILL-000029938_c@[users[p077020[appdata[local[temp[aptexport[40-07-02-76-repair-40-01-30-01-02-21-1-1-42.png" style="width: 85.0mm; height: 60.0mm;" translate="no"/><illusnum>RDE-000323273-07-02-76-repair-40-01-30-01-02-21-1-1-42-000029938</illusnum></figure><para translate="yes">Apply a bead of<ingredientname translate="yes">high performance structural adhesive</ingredientname>to the spare part.</para></descsection></descbody><description id="d1e330" translate="no"><title translate="yes">Fitting and adjusting the replaced parts</title><descbody translate="no"/><description id="d1e334" translate="no"><title translate="yes">Fitting and adjusting the replaced parts</title><descbody translate="no"><descsection translate="no"><marklayer translate="no"/><figure id="40-07-02-79-repair-40-01-30-01-02-21-1-1-43" translate="no"><image dimension="F1 (85x60) #" href="../MergedPictures/ILL-000029941_c@[users[p077020[appdata[local[temp[aptexport[40-07-02-79-repair-40-01-30-01-02-21-1-1-43.png" style="width: 85.0mm; height: 60.0mm;" translate="no"/><illusnum>RDE-000323273-07-02-79-repair-40-01-30-01-02-21-1-1-43-000029941</illusnum></figure></descsection><descsection translate="no"><marklayer translate="no"/><figure id="40-07-02-78-repair-40-01-30-01-02-21-1-1-44" translate="no"><image dimension="F1 (85x60) #" href="../MergedPictures/ILL-000029940_c@[users[p077020[appdata[local[temp[aptexport[40-07-02-78-repair-40-01-30-01-02-21-1-1-44.png" style="width: 85.0mm; height: 60.0mm;" translate="no"/><illusnum>RDE-000323273-07-02-78-repair-40-01-30-01-02-21-1-1-44-000029940</illusnum></figure><para translate="yes">Position the replacement part on the vehicle.</para></descsection><descsection translate="no"><marklayer translate="no"/><figure id="40-07-02-82-repair-40-01-30-01-02-21-1-1-45" translate="no"><image dimension="F1 (85x60) #" href="../MergedPictures/ILL-000030125_c@[users[p077020[appdata[local[temp[aptexport[40-07-02-82-repair-40-01-30-01-02-21-1-1-45.png" style="width: 85.0mm; height: 60.0mm;" translate="no"/><illusnum>RDE-000323273-07-02-82-repair-40-01-30-01-02-21-1-1-45-000030125</illusnum></figure><para translate="yes">Scrape off the surplus adhesive before it dries using the<toolref format="dita" href="x-wc://file=OS-000011764.xml" scope="external" translate="no" type="specifictool"><linkdesc translate="no">Levelling tool for bodywork seal</linkdesc><linkvalue translate="no">Car.1786</linkvalue></toolref>.</para></descsection><descsection translate="no"><marklayer id="marklayer-d1e357" translate="no"><mark id="MARK.REPAIR-40X01X30X01-02X21-1-1.3" translate="no"><mcomponent translate="no"><label translate="no"/></mcomponent><designation translate="no">2</designation></mark></marklayer><figure id="40-07-02-80-repair-40-01-30-01-02-21-1-1-46" translate="no"><image dimension="F1 (85x60) #" href="../MergedPictures/ILL-000031254_lay-000121105.png" style="width: 85.0mm; height: 60.0mm;" translate="no"/><illusnum>RDE-000323273-07-02-80-repair-40-01-30-01-02-21-1-1-46-000031254</illusnum></figure><figure id="40-07-02-81-repair-40-01-30-01-02-21-1-1-47" translate="no"><image dimension="F1 (85x60) #" href="../MergedPictures/ILL-000030124_lay-000121104.png" style="width: 85.0mm; height: 60.0mm;" translate="no"/><illusnum>RDE-000323273-07-02-81-repair-40-01-30-01-02-21-1-1-47-000030124</illusnum></figure><para translate="yes">Hold the replacement part with the locking pliers (at the front and rear cross members) and the<!--Arbortext, Inc., 1988-2015, v.4002--><?Pub Inc?><materialname otherprops="MAT25_EN" translate="yes" xml:lang="en" xsi:noNamespaceSchemaLocation="urn:ptc:names:renault:dita:xsd:materialname.xsd">safety strap(s)</materialname>to position it securely according to the markings made earlier<sieref href="x-wc://gie=OR:wt.part.WTPartMaster:3503961" translate="no"><linkdesc translate="no">body structure maintenance and adjustment tools : use</linkdesc><linkvalue translate="no">GIEMR-001610</linkvalue></sieref>(MR400, 05B, Bodywork equipment and tooling).</para><noteR translate="no" type="note"><para translate="yes">Note:</para><para translate="yes">To fit the safety straps without removing the quarter panel windows, use<technicalvalue translate="no"><value translate="yes">3</value></technicalvalue>safety straps.</para></noteR></descsection><para translate="yes">Let the adhesive dry for<technicalvalue translate="no"><value translate="yes">10 hours</value></technicalvalue>at an ambient temperature or for<technicalvalue translate="no"><value translate="yes">2 hours</value></technicalvalue>at<technicalvalue translate="no"><value translate="yes">60˚C</value></technicalvalue>.</para></descbody></description><description id="d1e415" translate="no"><title translate="yes">Making the other joints</title><descbody translate="no"><para translate="yes">Make the rest of the replacement part joints.</para></descbody></description></description><description id="d1e421" translate="no"><title translate="yes">Finishing after assembly</title><descbody translate="no"/><description id="d1e425" translate="no"><title translate="yes">Applying finishing product</title><descbody translate="no"><para translate="yes">Prime the side bonding areas.</para><descsection translate="no"><marklayer translate="no"/><figure id="40-07-02-82-repair-40-01-30-01-02-21-1-1-48" translate="no"><image dimension="F1 (85x60) #" href="../MergedPictures/ILL-000030125_c@[users[p077020[appdata[local[temp[aptexport[40-07-02-82-repair-40-01-30-01-02-21-1-1-48.png" style="width: 85.0mm; height: 60.0mm;" translate="no"/><illusnum>RDE-000323273-07-02-82-repair-40-01-30-01-02-21-1-1-48-000030125</illusnum></figure><para translate="yes">Apply a finishing seal, to the side bonding areas.</para><para translate="yes">Scrape off the surplus adhesive before it dries using the<toolref format="dita" href="x-wc://file=OS-000011764.xml" scope="external" translate="no" type="specifictool"><linkdesc translate="no">Levelling tool for bodywork seal</linkdesc><linkvalue translate="no">Car.1786</linkvalue></toolref>.</para></descsection></descbody></description></description></description></description>